In the following code we cannot get rid of some warning:

{code lang=Kotlin}
interface A
class B : A
fun foo1(list: List<A>, arg: B?): Boolean {
    // contains(T): Boolean is deprecated. Collection and element have incompatible types. Upcast element to Any? if you are sure
    return arg in list
}
fun foo2(list: List<A>, arg: B?): Boolean {
    // No cast needed
    return arg as A? in list
}
fun foo3(list: List<A>, arg: B?): Boolean {
    // No warning but KNPE risk
    return arg!! in list
}
// But
fun foo4(list: List<A>, arg: B): Boolean {
    // Ok
    return arg in list
}
{code}

Together it looks strange.